Bibliographic References: Atti XT CStMG 1971, pi. 111,2; ArchReps 1972Non Sepcified3, p. 34, fig. 1; LIMC II, p. 116, Aphrodite 1182, pi. 118,1
Imagery Description: Body: (a) Birth of Aphrodite—two Eileithyiai assist Aphrodite to rise; above an Eros flies with a piece of drapery in his hands, (b) nude youth bending forward in front of draped woman seated by stele. The lid consists of three main sections: (i) a lekanisNon Sepcifiedlike lid, with (ii) another lekanis on top of it and on top of that (iii) a lebes gamikos. (i) is decorated with (a) bird, (b) female head; (ii) and (iii) with female heads.
Artist: The Painter of Naples 2585 and his circle
